status.info: We use this protocol and it's working

steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"79l9q","text":"Harvest cells from 2 confluent wells of a 6 well plate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"87c8b","text":"Lyse aggregate-containing cells by vortexing in cold RIPA buffer (Thermo) supplemented with protease inhibitor cocktail (Roche) and DNase. 20 mM N-ethylmalemide should be included in the lysis buffer to inhibit the activity of deubiquitinating enzymes.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"s5tm","text":"Briefly sonicate lysate and centrifuge at 2,000 x g for 5 min to remove cell debris.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"11drc","text":"Collect supernatant, determine protein concentration and normalize across samples.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"3gvm4","text":"Dilute 1 mg protein in a total volume of 600 µL RIPA buffer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9vq0h","text":"Add 50 µL anti-GFP bead slurry (µMACS GFP Isolation kit, Miltenyi Biotec) to diluted lysate.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"5gj9e","text":"Incubate for 1 h at 4 °C in a rotating wheel at 10 rpm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"av07j","text":"Before the end of 1 h, place µ-columns (Miltenyi Biotec) in the magnetic field of a µMACS Separator (Miltenyi Biotec) and equilibrate columns by applying 250 µL RIPA buffer. Allow complete flow-through.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4h17f","text":"Apply cell lysates and beads to µ-columns. Allow complete flow-through.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
{"blocks":[{"key":"a5m3m","text":"Elute by applying 50 µL pre-heated (95 °C) 1x SDS sample buffer.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"63f5","text":"Analyze eluates by immunoblotting with antibodies against GFP or ubiquitin.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

title: Detection of Tau ubiquitylation
